fields.description:
I'm one of the developers of Confluence Slack Integration. We send notifications to Slack, if somebody updated blog or page. There's a checkbox in old editor "Notify watchers" and action in new editor "Publish without notifying watchers". It would be great to expose this to the webhooks payload, so we could rely on it and skip sending a notification if a user doesn't want to spam Slack channel with updates.

We also have a few users who want this feature. One of them:

{noformat}
It would be nice if confluence only updated edits when the notify watchers checkbox is checked like so: https://www.dropbox.com/s/11o544eyt1zdoqw/Screenshot%202018-09-19%2020.10.42.png?dl=0
{noformat}

If the Space Import failed for the first time, subsequence attempt will end up reporting the space key already exists,

 
{code:java}
A space with key newsnow already exists.{code}
However, the user has no way to delete this space, as it is not shown on the UI.

[https://splunk.paas-inf.net/en-US/app/search/search?sid=1540159887.49110_1B882A2F-D7FC-426F-B1FF-48A2E08A7873]

I noticed some of the exception messages are not in the English:
{code:java}
com.atlassian.confluence.importexport.ImportExportException: Пространство с ключом AB уже существует. com.atlassian.studio.confluence.importexport.SpaceImportTaskRunnerImpl.validateImport(SpaceImportTaskRunnerImpl.java:329) com.atlassian.studio.confluence.importexport.SpaceImportTaskRunnerImpl.doImport(SpaceImportTaskRunnerImpl.java:249) {code}
 

If we don't "fix" it, we might end up having error messages in different languages (not just Russian). This will make bug analysis difficult. It's like open up a pandora box.
